All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Applicant
The Applicant class represents a user who can apply for BTO housing projects.
ApplicantMenu
The ApplicantMenu class provides the user interface for applicant users.
ApplicationManager
The ApplicationManager class handles all BTO housing applications in the system.
ApplicationStatus
The ApplicationStatus enum represents the possible states of a BTO application throughout its lifecycle.
BTOApplication
The BTOApplication class represents an application for a Build-To-Order (BTO) flat.
BTOProject
The BTOProject class represents a Build-To-Order housing project in the BTOMS system.
Enquiry
The Enquiry class represents a question or request from an applicant about a BTO project.
EnquiryManager
The EnquiryManager class handles user enquiries about BTO projects.
FlatType
The FlatType enum represents the different types of BTO flat units available for application.
HDBManager
The HDBManager class represents administrators who manage BTO housing projects.
HDBManagerMenu
The HDBManagerMenu class provides the user interface for HDB manager users.
HDBOfficer
The HDBOfficer class represents HDB staff who handle flat booking for successful applicants.
HDBOfficerMenu
The HDBOfficerMenu class provides the user interface for HDB officer users.
IApplicationManager
The IApplicationManager interface defines the contract for managing BTO applications.
IEnquiryManager
The IEnquiryManager interface defines the contract for managing enquiries about BTO projects.
IProjectManager
The IProjectManager interface defines the contract for managing BTO projects.
IUserManager
The IUserManager interface defines the contract for user authentication and management.
MainMenu
The MainMenu class serves as the entry point for the BTO Management System.
MaritalStatus
The MaritalStatus enum represents the possible marital statuses of users in the system.
PasswordHasher
The PasswordHasher class provides utilities for secure password hashing and verification.
ProjectManager
The ProjectManager class manages all BTO housing projects in the system.
SystemLogger
The SystemLogger class provides utilities for logging system events and user activities.
TablePrinter
The TablePrinter class provides utilities for displaying formatted ASCII tables in the console.
User
The abstract User class serves as the base class for all user types in the BTO Management System.
UserManager
The UserManager class handles user authentication, session management, and user data persistence.
UserType
The UserType enum represents the different types of users in the BTO Management System.
